// frame_hero.su — a θ-PARAMETERIZED hero frame, rendered whole-frame in ONE
// substrate op. This is the render core of the warmer/colder "a1" steering demo
// (queue item 1a): a single parameter vector θ drives the composed hero, and
// because every θ component arrives as a per-pixel broadcast BUFFER, changing θ
// never recompiles — the optimizer just changes call arguments (the load-bearing
// fact from the a1 spec: runtime parameters, no recompile).
//
// The hero composes two whole-frame fields plus a background level:
//   glow = ones - invs * ((x - cx)^2 + (y - cy)^2)     // movable, scalable blob
//   ring = ones - ((x^2 + y^2) - radius)^2             // accent ring at |p|^2 = radius
//   hero = bg + bright*glow + accent*ring
//
// θ axes (each a length-(N*N) broadcast buffer the host builds from a scalar):
//   cx, cy   — glow centre (layout)
//   invs     — inverse scale of the glow (spread; larger = tighter blob)
//   bright   — glow brightness
//   radius   — ring radius (accent placement)
//   accent   — ring brightness (accent weight)
//   bg       — background level
// All composition is elementwise buffer arithmetic (hadamard + add) → one
// substrate pass over every pixel. Host reshapes the returned buffer and paints.
function vector hero(vector x, vector y, vector ones,
                     vector cx, vector cy, vector invs,
                     vector bright, vector radius, vector accent, vector bg) {
    vector dx = x - cx;
    vector dy = y - cy;
    vector r2 = hadamard(dx, dx) + hadamard(dy, dy);
    vector glow = ones - hadamard(invs, r2);
    vector rr = hadamard(x, x) + hadamard(y, y) - radius;
    vector ring = ones - hadamard(rr, rr);
    return bg + hadamard(bright, glow) + hadamard(accent, ring);
}

// Self-contained sanity entry: θ = centred glow, unit scale/brightness, no accent,
// no background → centre pixel = 0 + 1*(1 - 0) + 0*ring = 1.
function vector main() {
    return hero(make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0),
                make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0),
                make_real(1.0), make_real(0.5), make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0));
}
